<H3> <TI>   Kohl, Mitterrand Meet in Mulhouse 30 May </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kohl, Mitterrand Meet in Mulhouse 30 May </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU3005153594 Hamburg DPA in German 1434 GMT 30 May 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU3005153594 </F>
<F P=104>  Hamburg DPA </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Mulhouse (DPA) -- The 63d Franco-German summit 
opened in the Alsace city of Mulhouse on Monday [30 May] 
afternoon. After a welcome ceremony with military honors, French 
President Francois Mitterrand and Federal Chancellor Helmut Kohl 
met for a first round of talks. 
  As in the meeting that will follow between Kohl and French 
Prime Minister Edouard Balladur, talks will focus on European 
issues. In the parallel talks in Mulhouse, the numerous 
ministers of both countries will also discuss the coordination 
of policies in the EU Presidency that Germany will take over on 
1 July and pass on to France on 1 January 1995. 

</TEXT>

