<F P=103> AU2905174294 </F>
<F P=104>  Hamburg DPA </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] [Passage omitted] Government spokesman Dieter 
Vogel said Honecker's death did "not come as a surprise." In an 
interview with Deutschlandfunk, Vogel added: "We all knew that 
he had been ill with cancer for a long time, and one had to 
expect this end." Vogel could not officially confirm Honecker's 
alleged wish that his ashes be buried in Germany. "But if such 
a wish exists, it can probably be fulfilled, because there is no 
legal means of refusing this." 

</TEXT>

