<F P=100> AUSTRIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Klestil Meets With Uganda's Museveni </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Klestil Meets With Uganda's Museveni </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   EA2805203194 Kampala Radio Uganda Network in English 1700 
GMT 28 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> EA2805203194 </F>
<F P=104>  Kampala Radio Uganda Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] President Yoweri Museveni, who is now on an 
official visit to Austria, was yesterday received by the 
president of the Federal Republic of Austria, Dr. Thomas 
Klestil, at the Hofburg Palace in Vienna. The two leaders held 
talks centerd on bilateral relations between Uganda and Austria. 
Speaking to the press after the talks, President Klestil said 
that, although Austrian foreign policy is centered on Europe, 
President Museveni's official visit to his country is a proof 
that Uganda took a central place in Austrian relations with 
Africa. President Museveni on his part said he is pleased that 
Austria is assisting Uganda in the rehabilitation of the water 
system in Kampala and hospitals around the country. He 
emphasized that trade and investment, rather than aid for 
Uganda, are more durable and sustainable forms of cooperation 
between the two countries, and in this regard looks forward to 
increased Austrian collaboration, which he said will be centerd 
on business as well as other investment, to top up the abundant 
potential the country has. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

