<F P=106> [Report signed PVB: "Kurdish Office in Brussels"] </F>
  [Excerpt] An International Bureau of Solidarity with the 
(Kurdish) Democratic Party (DEP) was opened in Brussels on 
Thursday [26 May]. The Turkish Government threatens to ban the 
DEP. Five DEP parliamentarians have been accused of treason and 
separatism and might be sentenced to death. Yasar Kaya, DEP 
honorary president and founder, is the owner of the OZGUR GUNDEM 
(Free Agenda), which ceased publication after several trials and 
harassments. Brussels Bureau Director Kaya says that the Bureau 
aims at defending the rights of his people, seeking 
international solidarity, and serving as an information center. 
[passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

