<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    China Granted DM252 Million in Development Aid </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU3105163494 Munich SUEDDEUTSCHE ZEITUNG in German 31 May 94 
p 2 </F>

<F P=103> AU3105163494 </F>
<F P=104>  Munich SUEDDEUTSCHE ZEITUNG </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["epd"-signed report: "Bonn Providing DM252 Million for </F>
China"] 
  [Text] Bonn -- The Federal Government will provide the 
People's Republic of China with 252 million German marks [DM] in 
development aid this year. Development cooperation will 
continue to concentrate on the fight against poverty, protection 
of the environment and resources, and political education, the 
Ministry for Economic Cooperation said. Furthermore, as a 
result of this year's government talks in Beijing the Federal 
Government will subsidize China's economic reforms, as well as 
rural telecommunications and energy supply, which have been 
impairing economic development. It has been reported that in 
these talks the German delegation also pointed out the 
importance of individual human rights. Of the DM252 million, 
DM168 million will come in the form of low-interest loans, and 
DM84 million as an outright grant. 

</TEXT>

