<F P=106> ["pid" report: "Neo-Nazi Tourism to the East"] </F>
  [Text] Northeim -- Neo-Nazis from Lower Saxony are 
recruiting members in Saxony-Anhalt. According to information 
from the Office for the Protection of the Constitution in 
Magdeburg, Thorsten Heise, Lower Saxony chairman of the 
right-wing extremist Liberal Workers Party [FAP], is attempting 
to establish "FAP structures" in Saxony-Anhalt. The new center 
of the anticonstitutional party is Wernigerode in the Ostharz, 
said Wolfgang Heidelberg, head of the Office for the Protection 
of the Constitution in Saxony-Anhalt, where the FAP, which has 
between 400 and 600 members throughout Germany, established a 
regional circle of 60 members last week. However, the number of 
supporters appears to be even larger. Nevertheless there is no 
land organization in Saxony-Anhalt yet, but even in this land 
Heise leads FAP as a "provisional chairman." FAP bases itself 
on the 1920 program of the National Socialist German Workers 
Party [NSDAP]. 
  Because of constant violence usually caused by FAP 
supporters, the police are permanently on alert, said Heidelberg. 
  On Saturday [28 May], in Heise's home town of Northeim, 
there 
was a demonstration against FAP staged mainly by numerous groups 
from the autonomous sphere, but also Greens. 

</TEXT>

