<H3> <TI>   Cavaco Silva Protests Manila Conference Expulsions </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Cavaco Silva Protests Manila Conference Expulsions </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD3105151894 Lisbon Radio Renascenca in Portuguese to Europe 
1400 GMT 31 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD3105151894 </F>
<F P=104>  Lisbon Radio Renascenca </F>
<F P=105>  Portuguese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Prime Minister [Cavaco Silva] sent a verbal 
protest to the Philippine Government in connection with the 
expulsion of Portuguese representatives at the Manila conference 
on East Timor. This is the first government reaction to events 
involving the controversial conference under way in the 
Philippines. 
  [Begin Cavaco Silva recording] A few days ago the Portuguese 
Government presented a verbal note to the Philippine Government 
protesting the fact that visas were not granted to Portuguese 
people, including Portuguese deputies, enabling them to 
participate in the Manila conference. At the same time the 
Portuguese Government expresses its surprise at the fact that a 
country we consider to be friendly has bowed to pressure from a 
dictatorship -- the Indonesian dictatorship. 
  We expressed our surprise, our apprehension at the fact that 
obstacles were placed in the way of Portuguese citizens and 
foreign citizens who wanted to participate in the Manila 
conference. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

