  [Text] In comments for our station, Defense Minister Julian 
Garcia Vargas said that the blue helmets' humanitarian aid for 
the Bosnian conflict cannot go on forever if the parties in 
conflict do not reach a peace agreement. Julian Garcia Vargas. 
  [Begin Garcia Vargas recording] We have to establish a 
principle: We will set a reasonable period of presence and if 
this period does not lead to anything, if the negotiations do 
not make any progress, we will have to tell the parties that we 
do not want to stay there forever. 
  In two months, [corrects himself] in five months, we will 
have been there for two years, and I think that it is time to 
speak to our European partners and to discuss with them the fact 
that this cannot go on forever. [end recording] 

