<H3> <TI>   Greeks Fire Shots at Turks in Border Region </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Greeks Fire Shots at Turks in Border Region </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA0106071994 Nicosia Bayrak Radio in Turkish 1930 GMT 31 May 
94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0106071994 </F>
<F P=104>  Nicosia Bayrak Radio </F>
<F P=105>  Turkish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Greek Cypriots are continuing their border 
provocations and shooting incidents. The Greek Cypriot National 
Guardsmen fired 12 shots, in twos or threes, towards the Turkish 
Cypriot side in the Lefke [Lefka] [word indistinct] region at 
2045 today. No one was killed or injured by the shots, which 
were probably fired from automatic weapons. Soldiers attached 
to the Security Forces Command acted with a cool head and did 
not respond to the provocations, preventing the incident from 
escalating any further. 
  Turkish Cypriot authorities lodged a protest about the 
incident with the UN Peace Forces. The Greek Cypriots fired 
shots on the Turkish Cypriot borders on three different 
occasions in the past week. 

</TEXT>

