<F P=100> ITALY &amp; VATICAN CITY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Military Solution Ruled Out for Rwanda </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Military Solution Ruled Out for Rwanda </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0106112794 Rome RAI Televideo Teletext in Italian 0931 GMT 
1 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0106112794 </F>
<F P=104>  Rome RAI Televideo Teletext </F>
<F P=105>  Italian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The only road to resolving the serious crisis in 
Rwanda is that of trying to find a political solution. Any 
military solution must be ruled out. Foreign Minister Antonio 
Martino stated this when telling the Chamber of Deputies of the 
latest developments in the civil war in the African country. 
Martino said that Italy will continue to work for a peaceful 
solution under the aegis of the United Nations to stop the 
crisis from spreading to neighboring countries, starting with 
Burundi. 
  Martino announced that he will be sending Franco Rocchetta, 
deputy secretary for foreign affairs, to the African country 
within the next few days. 

</TEXT>

