<F P=100> ITALY &amp; VATICAN CITY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Berlusconi: Country Rejects Racism, Anti-Semitism </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Berlusconi: Country Rejects Racism, Anti-Semitism </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD3105211094 Rome RAI Televideo Teletext in Italian 1957 GMT 
31 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD3105211094 </F>
<F P=104>  Rome RAI Televideo Teletext </F>
<F P=105>  Italian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The government move to secure the arrest and 
extradition of former SS captain Erich Priebke "was dictated by 
a repudiation, which has deep roots in our country, of crimes 
against humanity, of racism, and of anti-Semitism." The 
declaration was made by Prime Minister Berlusconi to two 
representatives from the Simon Wiesenthal Center, Rabbi's 
Abraham Cooper and Simon Samuels, during a meeting at the prime 
minister's office. 
  Justice Minister Biondi gave assurances that the 
documentation asking for Priebke's extradition would be sent to 
Argentina within the next few days. 

</TEXT>

