<H3> <TI>   Cote d'Ivoire's $60 Million Debt Written Off </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Cote d'Ivoire's $60 Million Debt Written Off </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0106153894 Montreal Radio Canada International in English 
1330 GMT 1 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0106153894 </F>
<F P=104>  Montreal Radio Canada International </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Canadian Embassy in Abidjan says Ottawa has 
forgiven the West African country of the Ivory Coast a debt of 
60 million dollars U.S., and (?a) statement says another 60 
million dollars in debt will be rescheduled. Ivory Coast has a 
total foreign debt of 21 billion dollars, the highest per capita 
in the world. 

</TEXT>

