<H3> <TI>   Germany To Continue Supporting Russian Research </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Germany To Continue Supporting Russian Research </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0206084294 Berlin DDP/ADN in German 0818 GMT 2 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0206084294 </F>
<F P=104>  Berlin DDP/ADN </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From DDP/ADN's "Wirtschaftdienst-Ost" economic service] </F>
  [Text] Berlin (ADN) -- Germany will continue to give 
support to research in Russia. This will be mainly through 
cooperation and material support, Bernd Neumann, parliamentary 
state secretary in the German Research Ministry, said on 
Deutschlandfunk Berlin on Thursday [2 June]. The aim of the aid 
is to ensure that Russia's research potential, which is in some 
areas considerable, does not deteriorate completely. Neumann, 
who is now in Moscow, said many research institutions there are 
threatened with collapse because salaries can no longer be paid 
and there is no money for energy and material. 

</TEXT>

