  [Text] Madrid, 1 Jun (EFE) -- A car bomb exploded today in 
Madrid near where a brigadier general in the Spanish Army was 
murdered an hour before. 
  The police noted that initial reports indicate the car bomb 
caused no casualties. This is the second attack to take place 
on Valia Street, in downtown Salamanca, which had been cleared 
following the murder of the general. 

