<F P=100> CYPRUS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Foreign Minister Reviews Report </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Foreign Minister Reviews Report </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0106191994 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1750 GMT 1 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0106191994 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 1 Jun (MENA)-- Cypriot Foreign Minister 
Alexandros Mikhailidhis has stated that the report submitted 
today by UN Secretary General Dr. Butrus Butrus-Ghali on the 
Cyprus issue reflects the efforts the secretary general is 
making to work out a suitable formula for the 
confidence-building measures between the parties concerned. 
  The Cypriot minister told MENA that his country will study 
that report. He noted the importance of the secretary general's 
proposal to hold an international conference on the Cyprus 
issue, to adopt intensified measures to implement the UN 
resolutions, and to hold a meeting of the peace guarantors: 
Turkey, Britain, and Greece. 
  He added that the confidence-building measures will yield 
economic benefits for Turkish Cypriots, particularly if the 
Turkish Cypriot city of Famagusta is opened to both sides for 
the sake of touristic and trade development. 
  The Cypriot minister noted that the secretary general's 
report demands the opening of Nicosia airport to both sides. 
This will enable Turkish Cypriots to travel without any 
difficulties. 

</TEXT>

