<H3> <TI>   Papoulias, Russia's Kozyrev Agree on Bosnia, Cyprus, EU </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Papoulias, Russia's Kozyrev Agree on Bosnia, Cyprus, EU </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0106200394 Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network in 
Greek 1700 GMT 1 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC0106200394 </F>
<F P=104>  Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Greek </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Russian President Boris Yeltsin will visit Corfu 
during the European Union [EU] summit and will sign the 
EU-Russia cooperation agreement. Prime Minister Andreas 
Papandreou is expected to pay an official visit to Russia next 
fall. This became known after a meeting between Russian Foreign 
Minister Andrey Kozyrev and his Greek counterpart, Karolos 
Papoulias, which focused on problems in the Balkans, Cyprus, 
Turkish provocations in Istanbul, and Russia's relations with 
Greece and the EU. The two sides reconfirmed their excellent 
political relations and their identical views on the issues of 
the Balkans and Cyprus. 
  Both ministers insisted that it is necessary to maintain the 
rule of the Montreux Treaty on the passage of ships in the Black 
Sea Straits. Kozyrev said there are some difficulties in the 
development of bilateral economic relations but stressed there 
is political will to improve this sector. He added that the 
establishment of an association of [words indistinct] 
businessmen is being promoted within this framework and 
Papoulias will have a meeting with them. 
  Kozyrev said he is grateful for the work that the Greek 
Government has done so cooperation between EU and Russia will 
proceed. He added that significant events may happen in this 
sector through the end of the Greek presidency. 
  Papoulias described bilateral cooperation on issues of the 
Balkans as close and said the two countries have identical views 
on ways to resolve the Yugoslav crisis. 
  The foreign minister will meet the Russian patriarch tonight 
and will discuss his initiatives for peace in the Balkans. 

</TEXT>

