<F P=103> TA0106153094 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara ANATOLIA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Damascus, Syria June 1 (A.A.) -- A meeting of 
conciliation held recently in Turkey between the representatives 
of two rival northern Iraqi Kurdish groups was reported 
successful today. 
  Jalal Talabani, Patriotic Union of Kurdistan leader, 
described Monday's meeting [30 May] with Mas'ud Barzani, 
Kurdistan Democratic Party [KDP] leader, as `very successful.' 
  However, representatives of the KDP claimed that their 
problem was not discussed in full detail during the meeting. 
  Talabani told the Anatolian Agency in Damascus that claims 
that they violated a May 17 truce with the KDP were not true. 
  `A joint agreement was made in Silopi to implement the 
cease-fire,' Talabani said. 
  Talabani added that he would be happy to hold a planned 
meeting with Barzani, in Turkey at the earliest opportunity. 
  KDP officials said that they wanted to bring an end to the 
clashes in the region through democratic means and were hoping 
that Talabani comes to their region to sit at the negotiating 
table. 

</TEXT>

