<F P=100> TURKEY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Karayalcin Calls Report `Unjust' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Karayalcin Calls Report `Unjust' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA0106185994 Ankara TRT Television Network in Turkish 1700 
GMT 1 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0106185994 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara TRT Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Turkish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Announcer-read report] </F>
  [Text] Murat Karayalcin, state minister and deputy prime 
minister, has described the report issued by the UN secretary 
general -- without waiting for the results and despite all the 
efforts exerted by the Turkish Republic of Northern Cyprus 
[TRNC] to reduce the conflicts to a minimum -- as unjust. 
  In a written statement, Karayalcin drew attention to the 
fact 
that the report was issued when the TRNC informed the United 
Nations of its positive views, some of which involved certain 
sacrifices. Stressing that the accusations leveled at the 
Turkish Cypriot side regarding its lack of political will, 
despite its constructive and positive approach, cannot be 
received with understanding, Karayalcin added: No doubt 
peaceful results cannot be achieved in Cyprus through an 
approach that supports the views of one side and pressures the 
other to accept the same views. The UN secretary general should 
not expect this approach to be tolerated. Karayalcin added that 
it should be known that one can reach a realistic and viable 
solution in Cyprus only through the free will of the two sides 
and through negotiations. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

