<F P=100> GERMANY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Minesweeping Operations To Finish by `End of Year' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Minesweeping Operations To Finish by `End of Year' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0106122994 Cologne Deutschlandfunk Network in German 1100 
GMT 1 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU0106122994 </F>
<F P=104>  Cologne Deutschlandfunk Network </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Mine-sweeping operations along the former inner 
German border will be completed by the end of the year. This is 
what a spokesman for the responsible authority in Magdeburg told 
DDP. He said the blasters were primarily removing plastic mines 
with loads of up to 200 grams. Between 1961 and 1985, more than 
1.5 million mines were reportedly laid along the former border. 

</TEXT>

