BFN 

  [Text] The Netherlands says it might contribute troops to 
the United Nations force in Rwanda. Dutch Foreign Minister 
Pieter Kooijmans and Development Cooperation Minister Jan Pronk 
have told parliament that if the security situation in Rwanda 
improves, they might be prepared to send troops after all. The 
Hague has so far been reluctant to send troops because it fears 
that Rwandans might think the troops come from Belgium. 

