<F P=100> SPAIN </F>
<H3> <TI>   `Terrorist' Attacks Reported in Madrid 1 Jun </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    `Terrorist' Attacks Reported in Madrid 1 Jun </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Army General Dies </H4>

<F P=102> PA0106123694 Madrid EFE in Spanish 0741 GMT 1 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> PA0106123694 </F>
<F P=104>  Madrid EFE </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] Madrid, 1 Jun (EFE) -- Four shots fired by a man 
and woman ended the life Army Brigadier General Juan Jose 
Hernandez Rovira, the victim of a terrorist attack carried out 
in Madrid today. 
  The attack took place at 0845 (0645 GMT) as the general was 
leaving his home, located in a Salamanca neighborhood in the 
center of Madrid. A resident of a building near the site of the 
attack told EFE the general, the father of six children, lost 
his wife last year. Municipal police sources told EFE that the 
general, who was still alive after the shooting, was taken to a 
hospital but died on arrival. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

