<F P=106> [Unattributed article: "Vatican/Rwanda: Holy See Wants UN </F>
Security Zone at Kagbayi"] 
  [Text] (ANSA) New York, June 1 -- The Holy See on Wednesday 
[1 June] asked the United Nations Security Council to set up a 
security zone around Kabgayi, the religious community in 
southwestern Rwanda where an estimated 38,000 refugees of the 
Tutsi tribe have sought shelter from Hutu militias. 
  "To save 38,000 lives, the UN must declare Kabgayi a 
security 
zone and must ban the entry of armed units there," the Vatican's 
UN representative, Renato Raffaele Martino, said. 

