  [Text] Mulhouse (DPA) -- Germany and France want to make 
armament cooperation even more effective. During their 
discussions in Mulhouse on Tuesday [31 May] the two defense 
ministers, Volker Ruehe and Francois Leotard, came out in favor 
of building a new military cargo plane. The experience of the 
civilian aircraft producer Airbus Industries are to be used in 
this venture. 
  There is "a strategic demand" for the new cargo plane, which 
is to have a greater range than the current planes with a view 
to international missions, German delegation circles said. A 
study on the plans will be drawn up in the Western European 
Union by next year. 

</TEXT>

