<H3> <TI>   Council Adopts Directive on Hydrofuels </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Council Adopts Directive on Hydrofuels </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BR2705102994 London REUTER Textline Database in English 26 
May 94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> BR2705102994 </F>
<F P=104>  London REUTER Textline Database </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed article from Brussels EUROPE: "Energy Council </F>
Definitively Adopts Directive on Hydro-Fuels"] 
  [Text] The "Energy" Council adopted without debate on 
Wednesday [25 May] the directive on the conditions for granting 
and exercising authorizations to prospect, explore, and produce 
hydrofuels. 
  The main aim of this directive (adopted under the 
co-decision 
procedure with the EP) is to assure nondiscriminatory access to 
activities and thus promote competition in the sector. The 
principle adopted is that Member States own the sovereignty and 
sovereign rights to their hydrofuels resources (situated on 
their territory); national authorities consequently retain the 
right to designate those parts of their territories where 
prospection and exploitation can take place. But, each time an 
area is opened to the exercise of these activities, the Member 
State will be held responsible for ensuring that there is no 
discrimination between the different operators interested in 
access. The States will, however, be allowed to refuse, for 
"national security" reasons, access to operators which are 
effectively controlled by third countries or nationals of third 
countries. The States will have to conform to this directive at 
latest by 1 January 1995; the new authorizations granted by 
Denmark before 31 December 2012 are the subject of certain 
exemptions. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

