<H3> <TI>   Seized Plutonium Reportedly Weapons-Grade </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Seized Plutonium Reportedly Weapons-Grade </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2705130894 Hamburg DPA in German 1222 GMT 27 May 94--FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU2705130894 </F>
<F P=104>  Hamburg DPA </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] Stuttgart (DPA) -- The plutonium seized in 
Baden-Wuerttemberg in early May is weapons-grade material. As 
DPA learned from a well-informed source on Friday [27 May], the 
material, which was not recognized by the authorities for weeks, 
is 56 grams of plutonium-239 in powder form. According to the 
information, the highly poisonous material was found during the 
search of an apartment in Tengen near Konstanz in the course of 
investigations involving counterfeiting. [passage omitted] 
  So far, no information has been provided about the origin of 
the material. The Environment Ministry announced on Thursday 
that the material probably came from East Europe. The Land 
Office of Criminal Investigations (LKA) in Stuttgart, which is 
responsible for the investigations, has announced that it will 
issue a statement on Friday. The Konstanz Public Prosecutor's 
Office has not yet commented. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

