<H3> <TI>   President Scalfaro Receives Clinton at Quirinale Palace </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    President Scalfaro Receives Clinton at Quirinale Palace </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BR0206102994 Rome ANSAMAIL Database in English 0932 GMT 2 
Jun 94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> BR0206102994 </F>
<F P=104>  Rome ANSAMAIL Database </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed article: "Clinton at Quirinale Palace"] </F>
  [Excerpt] (ANSA) Rome, June 2 -- United States President 
Bill Clinton and his wife, Hillary, went to the presidential 
Quirinale Palace at mid-morning for talks with Italian head of 
State Oscar Luigi Scalfaro. 
  Clinton was met on his arrival by Scalfaro, accompanied by 
his daughter Marianna, and after the traditional playing of 
respective national anthems and a review of the guards retired 
in the Quirinale for their talks. 
  The American president began his day in Rome with a jog in 
the central Villa Borghese park, located close to the embassy 
residence of Villa Taverna, along with the Washington ambassador 
to Rome, Reginald Bartholomew. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

