<H3> <TI>   Israel To `Temporarily Freeze' Relations With Italy </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Israel To `Temporarily Freeze' Relations With Italy </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BR0206153494 Milan CORRIERE DELLA SERA in Italian 2 Jun 94 p 
1--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> BR0206153494 </F>
<F P=104>  Milan CORRIERE DELLA SERA </F>
<F P=105>  Italian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Israel To Freeze Its Relations With </F>
Rome"] 
  [Text] Jerusalem -- Israel has decided to temporarily 
freeze its relations with Italy. This came as a surprise move 
by [Israeli Prime Minister] Peres' deputy Yosi Beilin, intended 
as confirmation of Israel's condemnatory stance against the 
neofascist danger in Europe. The decision was made at the 
Israeli Foreign Ministry yesterday evening, following lengthy 
consultations, over a period of days with the Israeli Embassy in 
Rome. 
  Another plenary meeting is planned at the Foreign Ministry 
in 
Jerusalem for next week. It is being suggested that the 
complete freeze on relations may be lifted, and that the measure 
will only apply to AN [National Alliance] members. 
  A first practical measure was already taken yesterday with 
the decision to cancel a cultural mission to Rome, which was 
scheduled for early next week. Israeli Foreign Ministry sources 
explained: "We did not wish our representatives to meet the new 
Cultural Heritage Minister Domenico Fisichella, who is a 
National Alliance member." 
  The same sources added: "We had to choose between the logic 
of reasons of state, which leads us to greatly appreciate 
[Italian Foreign] Minister Martino's friendly statements 
concerning Israel, and our commitment to combat any kind of 
return to the totalitarian ideologies which developed in Europe 
in the first half of this century." 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-42407 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drweu107__a94043" </HT>


