<H3> <TI>   National Debt Continues To Increase </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    National Debt Continues To Increase </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BR2405142094 Rome ANSAMAIL Database in English 1411 GMT 23 
May 94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> BR2405142094 </F>
<F P=104>  Rome ANSAMAIL Database </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed article: "Debt Up, Public Sector Borrowing </F>
Requirement Down, Bank of Italy Says"] 
  [Excerpt] (ANSA) Rome, May 23 -- National debt continues to 
move inexorably upward, but the public sector borrowing 
requirement [PSBR] is showing signs of slowing down, according 
to figures released Monday [23 May] by the Bank of Italy. 
  The national debt is fast approaching the 1800 trillion lire 
(1.13 trillion dollar) mark, according to the Bank figures which 
do not take account of the state railways, monopolies or 
telephones, which have recently been turned into joint stock 
companies. Were these included, the total would come to 1825 
trillion lire (1.14 trillion dollars). 
  Efforts by successive governments to bring the PSBR into 
check, thus improving the debt/gross national product ratio, 
seem to be bearing fruit, however, the Bank said, with the 
borrowing requirement for the first three months of this year 
standing at 41.690 trillion lire (26.2 billion dollars), nine 
trillion lire (5.6 billion dollars) down on the same period of 
1993. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

