<F P=106> [Unattributed article: "Military Probably Will Be Sent to </F>
Rwanda"] 
  [Text] If the security situation in Rwanda improves, the 
Netherlands Government is after all prepared to contribute a 
unit of 20 military police to UN missions in the country. 
  A previous UN request was refused by the government, because 
the Netherlands had already provided enough soldiers for UN 
peacekeeping operations. The situation in Rwanda is also too 
dangerous, as Netherlands soldiers are likely to be mistaken for 
Belgians. Belgian soldiers have already been killed in Rwanda. 
The Second Chamber found the latter argument unconvincing. 

